problem_statement:
Support ternary operator in expression
### Description

Would be nice if Qute would support the ternary and elvis operator in an expression like this:

``` 
{#let test="hallo"}
        {test == "hallo" ? 'yes' : 'no'}
{/}
```

Currently it just works if a method is available on the object, like:

``` 
{#let test="hallo"}
        {test.equals("hallo") ? 'yes' : 'no'}
{/}
```

### Implementation ideas

_No response_

