problem_statement:
Resources path params not not included when a Sub-Resource is filtered by @ServerRequestFilter
### Describe the bug

Resources path params not not included in ContainerRequestContext/UriInfo when a Sub-Resource is filtered by ServerRequestFilter. 


### Expected behavior

When a Sub-Resource has path parameters inherited from the parent resource, when filtering with @ServerRequestFilter, the method getPathParameters() of UriInfo should provide all path parameters, including path params inherited from the parent resource.

### Actual behavior

When a Sub-Resource has path parameters inherited from the parent resource, when filtering with @ServerRequestFilter, the method getPathParameters() of UriInfo doesn't provide path params inherited from the parent resource, only path params of sub-resource.

### How to Reproduce?


@Path("/resources")
@Produces({MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON})
@ApplicationScoped
public class Resource { 

 @Inject SubResource subResource;

 @GET
  @Path("/{resourceId}")
  @SomeNameBindingAnnotition(SomeRole)
  public Uni<ResourceEntity> get(@RestPath String resourceId) {
    return Uni.createFrom().item(resource);
  }

 @Path("/{resourceId}/sub-resources")
  public SubResource setupSubResource() {
    return subResource;
  }
}

@ApplicationScoped
public class SubResource { 

 @GET
  @Path("/{subResourceId}")
  @SomeNameBindingAnnotition(SomeRole)
  public Uni<ResourceEntity> get(@RestPath String resourceId, @RestPath String subResourceId) {
    return Uni.createFrom().item(subResource);
  }
}

  @ServerRequestFilter()
  @SomeNameBindingAnnotition("")
  public Uni<Void> filter(
      ContainerRequestContext requestContext,
      UriInfo uriInfo) {
    // when filtering the sub resource, resourceId isn't included
    System.out.println("Path params" + uriInfo.getPathParameters());
  }

